Q1. Does the fold stay above 5x?
    7 of 11 bases have fold > 5x. Range: 0.8x - 80.6x.

Q2. Is the FOLD more stable than the P-VALUE?
    fold    spans 97.7x  (0.8 - 80.6)
    p_six   spans 8-fold  (0.0422 - 0.331)
    p_kotias spans 104-fold (0.00277 - 0.289)
    >> If the fold spans much less than the p-values, REPORT THE FOLD.

Q3. Does Test 3 still FIRE at aDNA-typical bases (~120k)?
  basis  p_six p_kotias   fold control_holds kotias_breaks
